    <section class="cookie-page-grid">
        <article class="app-panel cookie-page-panel">
            <div class="cookie-page-section-heading">
                <p class="cookie-page-section-eyebrow">Duration</p>
                <h2>Session and persistent storage</h2>
            </div>
            <ul class="cookie-page-list">
                <li><strong>Session cookies</strong> may expire when the browser is closed or when the active session times out.</li>
                <li><strong>Persistent cookies or browser storage</strong> can remain for a longer period so the platform or a third-party service can remember settings, measure visits, or keep service state across sessions.</li>
                <li>Retention can vary depending on the feature, provider, browser configuration, and whether a user clears stored site data manually.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <aside class="app-panel cookie-page-panel cookie-page-manage-panel">
            <p class="cookie-page-section-eyebrow">Control</p>
            <h2>How users can manage cookies</h2>
            <ul class="cookie-page-list cookie-page-list-compact">
                <li>Use browser settings to block, delete, or limit cookies and site data.</li>
                <li>Sign out of authenticated sessions when using shared devices.</li>
                <li>Use browser privacy controls or extensions to manage third-party technologies.</li>
                <li>Expect some login, preference, search, or embedded features to work less reliably if browser storage is disabled.</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="cookie-page-grid">
